720747f-a.title: Manhattan: Lafayette Street - Duane Street
720747f-a.text:
Lafayette Street, north from Duane Street (where tracks are seen), to
and including Leonard Street, showing the New York Edison Co. plant and
office building on the west side of the street extending from Duane to
Pearl Streets. Also shown are Nos. 520 to 514 Pearl Street (right fore-
ground), east from and including Lafayette, to but not including Centre
Streets. These houses and those extending on the east side of Lafayette
north to Worth Street were later demolished to make way for a small park.
In the centre background is visible part of the New York Life Insurance
Co. Building (with clock-tower) occupying the block from Catherine Lane
to Leonard Street.
December 1925.
Brown Brothers.
720747f-a.folder: Lafayette Street & Duane Street, Manhattan, NY

720743f-a.title: Manhattan: Lafayette Street - Reade Street
720743f-a.text:
Lafayette Street (right), north from and including Reade, to but not
including Pearl Streets, showing the 21-story Court Square Building
(No. 2 Lafayette Street) from Reade to Duane Streets. Also shown (left)
is Reade Street, west from Lafayette Street with a portion of the Hall
of Records visible in the foreground. The New York Edison Co. plant and
office building is shown extending from Duane to Pearl Streets (side wall
with sign on it), and on Duane Street, north side, from Lafayette to Elm
Streets.
1926.
Photograph submitted by the Court Square Building Inc.
720743f-a.folder: Lafayette Street & Reade Street, Manhattan, NY

720746f-a.title: Manhattan: Lafayette Street - Reade Street
720746f-a.text:
Lafayette Street, west side, (right), north from and including Reade,
to and including Leonard Streets, showing work in progress on the foundation
for the new 21-story Court Square Building, adjoining the 10-story Jones
Building (only the rear of which is shown), from Reade to Duane Streets.
Also shown is the New York Edison Co. office building and plant, from
Duane to Pearl Streets. In the left foreground is seen Reade Street, north
side, west from Lafayette, to and including Elm Streets. The New ork
LLife Insurance Co. Building (with clock-tower) is visible in the right
background occupying the block from Catherine Lane to Leonard Street.
1926.
Photograph Submitted by the Court Square Building Inc.
